text: Antoine de Bourbon, duc de Vendôme, also called Antoine of Navarre (22 April 1518 – 17 November 1562) was the King of Navarre through his marriage (jure uxoris) to Queen Jeanne III, from 1555 until his death.Detlev Schwennicke, Europaische Stammtafeln, Neue Folge, Band II (Marburg: J. A. Saargardt, 1984), Tafel 28 He was the founder of the Royal House of Bourbon.The British Cyclopedia of Biography, Vol 1, ed. Charles Frederick Partington (London: W. Orr, 1837), p. 291 Antoine was the father of Henry IV of France. == References == Category:1518 births Category:1562 deaths Category:House of Bourbon Category:Navarrese monarchs
title: Antoine of Navarre
